Here’s how I reached there in just 2 months 👇

1. Trained 6 days a week — no matter what.
I didn’t wait for motivation. I followed a split that hit every muscle group with enough intensity and recovery. Push, pull, legs, core — on repeat.

2. Ate clean and stuck to basics.
No crash diets, no extremes. High protein, balanced meals, and consistency. The goal was fat loss with muscle retention — and it worked.

3. Cardio wasn’t optional.
20 minutes post-workout walk on treadmill and hitting 10k steps every day. Helped stay lean and accelerate the fat loss process without burning out.

4. Slept like it was part of the workout.
7–8 hours daily. No late-night scrolling. Recovery matters just as much as the grind — that’s how you preserve muscle while shredding.

5. Tracked everything.
From macros to sets, I documented progress every week. Seeing numbers change is powerful. It keeps you accountable, sharp, and focused.
